title: Drawing, ""Conch Divers"", 1885–86
inscribed: Recto: Inscribed in graphite beneath the framing line of the top image: Conch Divers
creditline: Gift of Charles Savage Homer, Jr.
description:
Recto:  Vertical view at top of an African-American male and youth in a rowboat, across the stern of which is a dead shark, with a sailing boat visible on the horizon, at left; and at center, drawn in the opposite direction and invalidated is the bust of an African-American male shown in profile.

Verso:  Horizontal view of a diver on the floor of the sea, with sea plants and fish and the under side of a boat.

tombstone.epitaph:
Drawing, ""Conch Divers"", 1885–86.
1885–86. Graphite on paper. Gift of Charles Savage Homer, Jr.. 1912-12-250.
